== Trichy Assault Rifle 2011 ==

The OFB has stated that the TAR 2011 is different from the AK-47 right? So... why does it still link to AK-47? -- [[User:Anurag2k12|Anurag2k12]] ([[User talk:Anurag2k12|talk]]) 18:17, 20 August 2012 (UTC)

:Hi Anurag,
:I'm very pleased to learn that you took time to go through the links provided. Trichy Assault Rifle (TAR) is an improved variant of AK-47 and has the fastest firing rate of 800 rounds/minute compared to the standard 600 rounds/minute of AK-47 in the burst mode. However, it became the problem as it caused stoppages so it was finally reduced to 650 rounds/minute which is again significantly higher than that of AK-47s. Overall, it's a variant of AK-47, you can even see it listed in [[AK-47]]'s variant section. You may also want to look at the references to TAR in OFT's article which are
[http://www.spsmai.com/military/?id=7&q=Tiruchi-ordnance-factory-develops-new-assault-rifle  	Tiruchi ordnance factory develops new assault rifle] [http://www.asian-defence.net/2011/03/indian-tiruchi-ordnance-factory.html Indian Tiruchi Ordnance Factory Develops New Assault Rifle Like AK-47] [http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-01-14/nagpur/30627285_1_ak-47-insas-new-rifle Indian 'AK-47' too fast for its own good]. Please help to report any errors you come across or simply modify yourself. Thanks a lot for your efforts!
